label.value: Metastatic Vaginal Adenocarcinoma

value.value: An adenocarcinoma that arises from the vagina and has metastasized to other anatomic sites.

label.value: Vulvar Cancer pM1 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Vulvar cancer with distant metastasis (including pelvic lymph node metastasis). (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Vulvar Cancer Clinical TNM Finding v7

value.value: A clinical finding about one or more characteristics of vulvar cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system.

label.value: Vulvar Cancer Clinical Distant Metastasis TNM Finding v7

value.value: A clinical finding about one or more characteristics of vulvar cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to distant metastases.

label.value: Vulvar Cancer cM0 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Vulvar cancer without evidence of distant metastasis. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Vulvar Cancer cM1 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Vulvar cancer with distant metastasis (including pelvic lymph node metastasis). (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Stage 0 Vulvar Cancer AJCC v7

value.value: Stage 0 includes: Tis, N0, M0.  Tis: Carcinoma in situ (preinvasive carcinoma). N0: No regional lymph node metastasis.  M0: No distant metastasis. FIGO no longer includes stage 0. (AJCC 7th ed.)

label.value: Piece Unit

value.value: A separate or limited portion or quantity of something that cannot be satisfactorily described using Dosage Form, Package Type, or Unit of Measurement terms: a piece of gum.

label.value: Stage I Vulvar Cancer AJCC v7

value.value: Stage I includes: T1, N0, M0. T1: Invasive vulvar cancer confined to the vulva or perineum. N0: No regional lymph node metastasis.  M0: No distant metastasis. (AJCC 7th ed.)

label.value: Stage IA Vulvar Cancer AJCC v7

value.value: Stage IA includes: T1a, N0, M0. T1a: Tumor confined to the vulva and perineum, 2 cm or less in greatest dimension, and with stromal invasion no greater than 1 mm.  N0: No regional lymph node metastasis.  M0: No distant metastasis. (AJCC 7th ed.)

label.value: Stage IB Vulvar Cancer AJCC v7

value.value: Stage IB includes: T1b, N0, M0.  T1b: Vulvar cancer with tumor size greater than 2 cm, or any size with stromal invasion more than 1.0 mm, confined to the vulva or perineum.  N0: No regional lymph node metastasis.  M0: No distant metastasis. (AJCC 7th ed.)

label.value: Metastatic Prostate Adenocarcinoma

value.value: An adenocarcinoma that arises from the prostate gland and has spread to other anatomic sites.

label.value: Talpidae Family Mole

value.value: A small, mammal of the family Talpidae that lives underground and feeds on small invertebrates. The mole has tiny covered eyes that are believed to be able to distinguish night from day, and not much else.

label.value: Stage II Vulvar Cancer AJCC v7

value.value: Stage II includes: T2, N0, M0.  T2: Vulvar cancer with tumor of any size with extension to adjacent perineal structures (lower/distal 1/3 urethra, lower/distal 1/3 vagina, anal involvement).  N0: No regional lymph node metastasis.  M0: No distant metastasis.  (AJCC 7th ed.)

label.value: Stage III Vulvar Cancer AJCC v7

value.value: Stage III includes: IIIA: (T1/T2, N1a/N1b, M0); IIIB: (T1/T2, N2a/N2b, M0); IIIC: (T1/T2, N2c, M0).  T1: Invasive vulvar cancer confined to the vulva or perineum.  T2: Vulvar cancer with tumor of any size with extension to adjacent perineal structures (lower/distal 1/3 urethra, lower/distal 1/3 vagina, anal involvement).  N1a: Vulvar cancer with one or two lymph node metastasis each measuring 5 mm or less.  N1b: Vulvar cancer with one lymph node metastasis measuring 5 mm or greater.  N2a: Vulvar cancer with three or more lymph node metastases each measuring 5 mm or less.  N2b: Vulvar cancer with two or more lymph node metastases measuring 5 mm or greater.  N2c: Vulvar cancer with lymph node metastasis with extracapsular spread.  M0: No distant metastasis.  (AJCC 7th ed.)

label.value: Stage IV Vulvar Cancer AJCC v7

value.value: Stage IV includes: IVA: (T1/T2, N3, M0); (T3, Any N, M0); IVB: (Any T, Any N, M1).  T1: Invasive vulvar cancer confined to the vulva or perineum.  T2: Vulvar cancer with tumor of any size with extension to adjacent perineal structures (lower/distal 1/3 urethra, lower/distal 1/3 vagina, anal involvement).  T3: Vulvar cancer with tumor of any size with extension to any of the following: upper/proximal 2/3 urethra, upper/proximal 2/3 vagina, bladder mucosa, rectal mucosa, or fixed to pelvic bone.  N3: Vulvar cancer with fixed or ulcerated regional lymph node metastasis.  M1: distant metastasis (including pelvic lymph node metastasis).  (AJCC 7th ed.)

label.value: Stage IVA Vulvar Cancer AJCC v7

value.value: Stage IVA includes: (T1/T2, N3, M0); (T3, Any N, M0).  T1: Invasive vulvar cancer confined to the vulva or perineum.  T2: Vulvar cancer with tumor of any size with extension to adjacent perineal structures (lower/distal 1/3 urethra, lower/distal 1/3 vagina, anal involvement).  T3: Vulvar cancer with tumor of any size with extension to any of the following: upper/proximal 2/3 urethra, upper/proximal 2/3 vagina, bladder mucosa, rectal mucosa, or fixed to pelvic bone.  N3: Vulvar cancer with fixed or ulcerated regional lymph node metastasis.  M0: No distant metastasis.  (AJCC 7th ed.)

label.value: Vaginal Cancer TNM Finding v7

value.value: A finding about one or more characteristics of vaginal cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system.

label.value: Vaginal Cancer Pathologic TNM Finding v7

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of vaginal cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system.

label.value: Vaginal Cancer Pathologic Primary Tumor TNM Finding v7

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of vaginal cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to staging of the primary tumor.

label.value: Vaginal Cancer pTX TNM Finding v7

value.value: Vaginal cancer in which the primary tumor cannot be assessed. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Vaginal Cancer pT0 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Vaginal cancer with no evidence of primary tumor. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Metastatic Prostate Carcinoma

value.value: A carcinoma that arises from the prostate gland and has spread to other anatomic sites.

label.value: Vaginal Cancer pTis TNM Finding v7

value.value: Vaginal cancer with a finding of carcinoma in situ. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Vaginal Cancer pT1 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Vaginal cancer with a tumor confined to vagina. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Vaginal Cancer pT2 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Vaginal cancer invading the paravaginal tissues but not the pelvic wall. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Vaginal Cancer pT3 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Vaginal cancer extending to the pelvic wall.  Pelvic wall is defined as muscle, fascia, neurovascular structures, or skeletal portions of the bony pelvis.  (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Vaginal Cancer pT4 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Vaginal cancer invading the mucosa of the bladder or rectum and/or extending beyond the true pelvis (bullous edema is not sufficient evidence to classify a tumor as T4).  (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Vaginal Cancer Pathologic Regional Lymph Nodes TNM Finding v7

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of vaginal cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to staging of regional lymph nodes.

label.value: Vaginal Cancer pNX TNM Finding v7

value.value: Vaginal cancer in which regional lymph nodes cannot be assessed. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Vaginal Cancer pN0 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Vaginal cancer without regional lymph node metastasis. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Vaginal Cancer pN1 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Vaginal cancer with pelvic or inguinal lymph node metastasis. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Stage I Prostate Adenocarcinoma AJCC v7

value.value: Stage I includes: (T1a-c, N0, M0, PSA less than 10, Gleason equal or less than 6); (T2a, N0, M0, PSA less than 10, Gleason equal or less than 6); (T1-2a, N0, M0, PSA X, Gleason X).  T1a: Tumor incidental histologic finding in 5% or less of tissue resected.  T1b: Tumor incidental histologic finding in more than 5% of tissue resected.  T1c: Tumor identified by needle biopsy (e.g., because of elevated PSA).  T2a: Tumor involves one-half of one lobe or less. cN0: No regional lymph node metastasis.  pN0: No positive regional nodes.  M0: No distant metastasis.  Gleason Equal or Less than 6: Well differentiated (slight anaplasia).  Gleason X: Gleason score cannot be processed.  (AJCC 7th ed.)

label.value: Vaginal Cancer Pathologic Distant Metastasis TNM Finding v7

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of vaginal cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to distant metastases.  There is no pathologic M0 for vaginal cancer.

label.value: Vaginal Cancer pM1 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Vaginal cancer with distant metastasis.  (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Vaginal Cancer Clinical TNM Finding v7

value.value: A clinical finding about one or more characteristics of vaginal cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system.

label.value: Vaginal Cancer Clinical Distant Metastasis TNM Finding v7

value.value: A clinical finding about one or more characteristics of vaginal cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to distant metastases.

label.value: Vaginal Cancer cM0 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Vaginal cancer without evidence of distant metastasis. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Vaginal Cancer cM1 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Vaginal cancer with distant metastasis. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Stage 0 Vaginal Cancer AJCC v7

value.value: Stage 0 includes: Tis, N0, M0.  Tis: Carcinoma in situ (preinvasive carcinoma). N0: No regional lymph node metastasis.  M0: No distant metastasis.  FIGO no longer includes stage 0. (AJCC 7th ed.)

label.value: Cervical Cancer TNM Finding v7

value.value: A finding about one or more characteristics of cervical cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system.

label.value: Cervical Cancer Clinical TNM Finding v7

value.value: A clinical finding about one or more characteristics of cervical cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system.  Because many patients are treated by radiation and never undergo surgical-pathologic staging, clinical staging provides uniformity and is preferred.  (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Cervical Cancer Clinical Primary Tumor TNM Finding v7

value.value: A clinical finding about one or more characteristics of cervical cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to staging of the primary tumor.

label.value: Stage II Prostate Adenocarcinoma AJCC v7

value.value: Stage II includes: IIA (T1a-c, N0, M0, PSA less than 20, Gleason 7); (T1a-c, N0, M0, PSA equal or more than 10 and less than 20, Gleason equal or less than 6); (T2a, N0, M0, PSA less than 20, Gleason equal or less than 7); (T2b, N0, M0, PSA less than 20, Gleason equal or less than 7); (T2b, N0, M0, PSA X, Gleason X); IIB (T2c, N0, M0, Any PSA, Any Gleason); (T1-2, N0, M0, PSA equal or more than 20, Any Gleason); (T1-2, N0, M0, Any PSA, Gleason equal or more than 8).  T1a: Tumor incidental histologic finding in 5% or less of tissue resected.  T1b: Tumor incidental histologic finding in more than 5% of tissue resected.  T1c: Tumor identified by needle biopsy (e.g., because of elevated PSA).  T2a: Tumor involves one-half of one lobe or less.  T2b: Tumor involves more than one-half of one lobe, but not both lobes.  T2c: Tumor involves both lobes.  cN0: No regional lymph node metastasis.  pN0: No positive regional nodes.  M0: No distant metastasis.  Gleason 7: Moderately differentiated (moderate anaplasia).  Gleason Equal or Less than 6: Well differentiated (slight anaplasia).  Gleason equal or more than 8: Poorly differentiated/undifferentiated (marked anaplasia).  (AJCC 7th ed.)

label.value: Cervical Cancer cTX TNM Finding v7

value.value: Cervical cancer in which primary tumor cannot be assessed. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Cervical Cancer cT0 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Cervical cancer with no evidence of primary tumor. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Cervical Cancer cTis TNM Finding v7

value.value: Cervical cancer with a finding of carcinoma in situ. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Cervical Cancer cT1 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Cervical cancer confined to uterus (extension to corpus should be disregarded). (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Cervical Cancer cT1b TNM Finding v7

value.value: Cervical cancer with clinically visible lesion confined to the cervix. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Cervical Cancer cT1b1 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Cervical cancer with clinically visible lesion 4.0 cm or less in greatest dimension confined to the cervix. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)
